.TH "batadv_frag_skb_fwd" 9 "batadv_frag_skb_fwd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_frag_skb_fwd \- forward fragments that would exceed MTU when merged
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_frag_skb_fwd
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *recv_if "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_orig_node *orig_node_src "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
skb to forward
.IP "recv_if" 12
interface that the skb is received on
.IP "orig_node_src" 12
originator that the skb is received from
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Look up the next-hop of the fragments payload and check if the merged packet
will exceed the MTU towards the next-hop. If so, the fragment is forwarded
without merging it.
.SH "RETURN"
true if the fragment is consumed/forwarded, false otherwise.
